2 Model

원래 코드에는 Exams_1.txt과 Exams_1J.txt의 두 개의 모델 파일이 있다. phi ~ dbeta(1,1)I(0.5,1)와 phi ~ dunif(0.5,1)만 다르지만 결과는 거의 같다.

k <- c(21,17,21,18,22,31,31,34,34,35,35,36,39,36,35)
p <- length(k) #number of people
n <- 40 # number of questions

data <- list("p", "k", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS
myinits <-  list(
  list(phi = 0.75, z = round(runif(p)))) # Initial group assignment

parameters <- c("phi","z") # parameters to be monitored:    

model_text <- "
# Exam Scores
model{
  # Each Person Belongs To One Of Two Latent Groups
  for (i in 1:p){
    z[i] ~ dbern(0.5)
  }
  # First Group Guesses
  psi <- 0.5
  
  # Second Group Has Some Unknown Greater Rate Of Success
  phi ~ dbeta(1,1)I(0.5,1)
  
  # Data Follow Binomial With Rate Given By Each Person's Group Assignment
  for (i in 1:p){
    theta[i] <- equals(z[i],0)*psi+equals(z[i],1)*phi
    k[i] ~ dbin(theta[i],n)
  }
}
"

samples <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                 n.chains=1, n.iter=10000, 
         n.burnin=1, n.thin=1, DIC=T)

아래는 Knowledge 집단의 \(\phi\) 분포이다.

plot_post(p1$phi, main = "phi", xlab = expression(phi), quietly = TRUE)

아래 그림에서 zi는 0이나 1의 값만 가진다. 그런 경우에 표준편차를 오류막대로 제시하는 것이 적절하지 않지만, 불확실성을 표시하기에 충분하다고 생각하였다.

p1 %>% pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("z"),
                    names_to = "SID",
                    values_to = "Value") %>% 
  group_by(SID) %>% 
  summarise(Mean = mean(Value),
            SD = sd(Value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  separate(col = 'SID', c(NA, "Participant")) %>% 
  mutate(Participant = as.numeric(Participant)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Participant, y = Mean)) +
  geom_point(color = "darkred", size = 3) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=ifelse(Mean-SD<0,0,Mean-SD), 
                    ymax=ifelse(Mean+SD>1,1,Mean+SD)), width=.2, color = "darkred") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(1, 15, by = 1)) +
  labs(title = expression(paste(italic(z)))) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

4 Exercise 6.1.4

우연수준보다 저조한 점수를 받을 수 있다면? phi의 초기값과 사전분포를 수정했다.

k <- c(21,17,21,18,22,31,31,34,34,35,35,36,39,36,35)
p <- length(k) #number of people
n <- 40 # number of questions

data <- list("p", "k", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS

  list(phi = 0.5, z = round(runif(p)))) # Initial group assignment

# Exam Scores
model{
  # Each Person Belongs To One Of Two Latent Groups
  for (i in 1:p){
    z[i] ~ dbern(0.5)
  }
  # First Group Guesses
  psi <- 0.5
  
  # Second Group Has Some Unknown Greater Rate Of Success
  phi ~ dunif(0, 1)
  
  # Data Follow Binomial With Rate Given By Each Person's Group Assignment
  for (i in 1:p){
    theta[i] <- equals(z[i],0)*psi+equals(z[i],1)*phi
    k[i] ~ dbin(theta[i],n)
  }
}
"

5 Exercise 6.1.5

Knowledge 집단일 사전확률을 90%로 정하고, 28점 한 명을 추가해보자. Exercise 6.1.3과 비교하자.

k <- c(21,17,21,18,22,31,31,34,34,35,35,36,39,36,35, 28)
p <- length(k) #number of people
n <- 40 # number of questions

data <- list("p", "k", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS
myinits <-  list(
  list(phi = 0.75, z = round(runif(p)))) # Initial group assignment

parameters <- c("phi","z") # parameters to be monitored:    

model_text <- "
# Exam Scores
model{
  # Each Person Belongs To One Of Two Latent Groups
  for (i in 1:p){
    z[i] ~ dbern(0.9)
  }
  # First Group Guesses
  psi <- 0.5
  
  # Second Group Has Some Unknown Greater Rate Of Success
  phi ~ dunif(0.5,1)
  
  # Data Follow Binomial With Rate Given By Each Person's Group Assignment
  for (i in 1:p){
    theta[i] <- equals(z[i],0)*psi+equals(z[i],1)*phi
    k[i] ~ dbin(theta[i],n)
  }
}
"

samples5 <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                 n.chains=1, n.iter=10000, 
         n.burnin=1, n.thin=1, DIC=T)
